---
description: Naming conventions for the repository
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Use consistent naming across frontend and backend.

Frontend:
- React components: PascalCase
- hooks: useXxx
- utility functions: camelCase
- feature folders: kebab-case or feature-name consistently
- types/interfaces: PascalCase
- constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE only for true constants

Backend Rust:
- files/modules: snake_case
- structs/enums/traits: PascalCase
- functions: snake_case
- constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

Naming rules:
- prefer explicit names over short names
- names must reflect business meaning, not implementation accident
- avoid vague names like data, info, handler, helper, manager unless scoped clearly
- avoid abbreviations unless industry-standard
- boolean names should read as booleans:
  - isLoading
  - hasConflicts
  - canCommit
  - aiEnabled

Git domain naming:
- use repository, branch, commit, diff, status, review consistently
- do not mix stagedFiles with selectedFiles unless they are truly different concepts
- do not use gitData, repoStuff, aiData-like names